14th National Festival of Loyalty of Youth and Children Closes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- The 14th national festival of loyalty of youth and children which opened on February 11 was closed with due ceremony at the Central Youth Hall on April 15.
 A result of the jury of the festival was released at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the festival, divided into political, economic, artistic and sports ones, the Pyongyang city organization placed first in total and the South Hamgyong and South Phyongan Provincial organizations second and third. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commendations of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, a cup and prize banner were awarded to those organizations which proved successful. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the socialist youth league, in a closing address said that the festival served as a significant festival in which all the organizations of the league and youth and children fully showed their faith and rock-firm will to give full play to the wisdom and spirit of the Songun youth vanguard in the worthwhile struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation   under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, holding President Kim Il Sung in high esteem for all ages as the sun of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the ceremony were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and others.

Reception Given for Overseas Koreans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- A reception arranged by leader  Kim Jong Il for overseas Koreans on the occasion of the Day of the Sun, was given at the Mansudae Art Theatre on April 15.
 Present there were delegations of Koreans in Japan, the General Association of Koreans in China, the Federation of Koreans in the U.S., the International United Confederation of Koreans, the Federation of Koreans in Canada, the Federation of Koreans in Australia, the Society for Cooperation among Koreans in Germany and the Patriotic Woodland of Chongryon (General Association of Korean Residents in Japan) and other overseas Koreans on a visit to the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, in a speech said that the whole life of President Kim Il Sung shine brightly as a history of a peerlessly great man who devoted himself only to the country's prosperity, people's happiness and the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal revolutionary exploits of the President are being successfully carried forward by Kim Jong Il, who is identical with the President in ideology, leadership, will, grit, personality and virtue, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed expectation that all the overseas Koreans would as ever hold the President in high esteem forever as the sun of Juche, build up their organizations under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, and actively contribute to the sacred cause of patriotism for the prosperity of the socialist homeland and reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ho Jong Man, chief vice-chairman of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee who is head of the delegation of Koreans in Japan, in a speech said that, enjoying the benevolent reception on the Day of the Sun, he longed for the President more ardently and looked back on the noble life of the President devoted to the overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that all the Koreans overseas are glorifying the dignity and honor of being overseas citizens of Songun Korea, enjoying great love generation after generation under the loving care of Kim Jong Il, illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu and the bright sun in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the overseas Koreans will firmly defend and preserve the patriotic tradition and heritage provided by the President, keeping in mind more deeply the confidence that eternal victory is in store for them on the road of Juche following the great sun, and strengthen all the organizations of overseas Koreans as overseas compatriots organizations of Juche type,he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An art performance was given there.

U.S. Moves to Establish MD under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- Kadish, director of the Missile Defence Agency of the U.S. Defence Department, at a recent sub-committee meeting of the U.S. House Armed Services Committee called for pushing forward  the establishment of the Missile Defence System (MD), saying that "governments and companies around the world are expressing greater interests in participating in the widening effort to develop defenses against ballistic missiles. "
 Commenting on this Minju Joson today says that the U.S. MD moves aimed to establish the sphere of military domination over the world would only spark off a new arms race and strain the situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is clearly proved by the recent situation of the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now shipping update war means into the Korean peninsula and surrounding areas under the pretext of "missile defence" in a bid to stifle the DPRK by force of arms and put its Asia strategy into practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These moves are laying a big stumbling block in the way of seeking a peaceful negotiated settlement of the nuclear issue and are placing the Korean peninsula on the tense situation on the eve of  the outbreak of the second Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no guarantee that this would not become another source of threatening Northeast Asian and global peace and security beyond the boundary of the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the peace-loving people of the world should see through the aggressive and dangerous nature of the Bush group��s reckless moves to establish the MD and keep sharper vigilance against the U.S., the commentary concludes.

Evening Gala and Art Performance Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- An evening gala was held by youth and students in Pyongyang and an art performance was given by schoolchildren to commemorate the Day of the Sun.
 Evening gala of youth and students in Pyongyang took place at Kim Il Sung Square.
 Senior officials of the Party, state and army and chairpersons of the friendly parties took the platform. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were overseas compatriots on a visit to the socialist homeland, diplomatic envoys and staff members of the foreign embassies here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants danced to the tune of such songs as "We Sing of Our Homeland Holding Leader in High Esteem," "We Visit Mangyongdae," "Our General Is Best" and "My Country Is a Large Family of Songun," turning the square into the sea of dancers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Overseas compatriots and foreign guests joined the dancers, adding to the festive mood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And evening galas of youth and students were held in every province, city and county yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A performance was given by the art circle members of the Mangyongdae Schoolchildren's Palace at the palace and a performance of the 43rd National Art Festival of Schoolchildren was held at the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were appreciated by senior Party and state officials, chairpersons of the friendly parties and overseas compatriots on a visit to the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were diplomatic envoys and staff members of the foreign embassies here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers proudly sang of their great joy of significantly commemorating the April holiday, a jubilee common to the humankind, and their ardent yearning and unbounded reverence for President Kim Il Sung who took a warm care of the children, calling them "king" of the country.

Joint Meeting with Members of Delegations of Juche Idea Study Groups Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- A joint friendly meeting of members of the delegations of the Juche idea study groups was held in Pyongyang on Thursday to commemorate the Day of the Sun.
 Present there were Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea (IIJI), and his party, the delegation of the Secretariat of the IIJI headed by its Deputy Secretary General Sakae Araki, members of the delegations of the Juche idea study groups of different countries on a visit to the DPRK and Kim Yong Il, vice-chairman of the Korean Social Scientists' Association, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vishwanath in his speech said that April 15, 1912, was the day when the eternal sun of the humankind was born and President Kim Il Sung provided the today of Songun politics that guarantees the socialist cause and the bright future of the global cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that they are disciples of the President, the sun of Juche, and leader Kim Jong Il, he called upon all the participants to remain loyal to the cause of Juche to the end with the pride and self-confidence of being the followers of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Il in his speech said that the immortal revolutionary feats of the President will shine forever and the Korean people will dynamically struggle for the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche, upholding the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the participants significantly commemorated the Day of the Sun, a holiday common to the humankind, singing songs and dancing.

Day of Sun Commemorated in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- The Korean people and schoolchildren and students have significantly commemorated the Day of the Sun in Juche 93 (2004), 10 years after the cause of perpetuating the memory of the President started in Korea.
 On the occasion, working people from all walks of life, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army and schoolchildren and students visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace, the supreme temple of Juche, to pay tribute to President Kim Il Sung and laid floral baskets and bouquets before his statues on Mansu Hill in capital and at provincial seats, revolutionary battle sites and historical sites before taking the oath of pledge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean Revolution Museum where President's immortal revolutionary history and fighting exploits are on display and the sixth Kimilsungia Festival were visited by an endless stream of people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Colorful commemorative functions were held in different places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the Mansudae Art Troupe, the Pyongyang Circus, the Ensemble of the Ministry of the People's Security and other art groups and members of the art agitation squads of institutions and enterprises gave performances at different places of the capital including Mangyongdae, a sacred place of the revolution, the plaza of the Arch of Triumph, the fun fair on Mt. Taesong and the plaza of the Three Revolution Exhibition, adding to the festive mood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people in Jagang, North Hamgyong and Kangwon Provinces and Kaesong City and members of the Democratic Women's Union of Korea in Hamhung City presented peculiar large choruses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people and schoolchildren and students in Ryanggang, North Phyongan, North Hwanghae and South Hamgyong Provinces held song-presentation meetings, oath-taking gatherings, virtue story-telling sessions, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, colorful art performances, sports and amusement games and evening galas took place in all provinces, cities and counties, at factories, enterprises, cooperative farms and schools in commemoration of the Day of the Sun.

Kim Jong Il Sends Greetings to Syrian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, today sent a message of greetings to Bashar al-Assad, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Baath Arab Socialist Party and president of Syria, on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of its independence.
 The message extended warm congratulations to the president and the friendly Syrian government and people on the occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said that the Syrian Arab people have made many achievements in different fields to achieve the prosperity of the country under the correct leadership of the Baath Arab Socialist Party since its independence, an event of turning significance in the modern history of Syria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people extend full support and firm solidarity to the president and the Syrian Arab people in their just struggle to defend the sovereignty of the country and the dignity of the nation and seek a fair and comprehensive solution to the Mid-east issue, meeting the outsiders' challenge to prevent Syria from making progress, the message noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the conviction that the traditional friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would as ever grow stronger and develop and sincerely wished the president good health and happiness.

Kim Yong Nam Sends Greetings to Syrian President
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, today sent a message of greetings to Syrian President Bashar al-Assad on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the independence of Syria.
 The message extended warm congratulations to the president and the friendly Syrian government and people on the occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last 58 years since the independence of the country the Syrian Arab people have made many achievements in their efforts to defend the dignity of the nation and the sovereignty of the country and build a new prosperous society, the message said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are sincerely rejoiced over this and extend full support and solidarity to the Syrian Arab people in their just cause to achieve the country's progress and modernization and solve the Mid-east issue fairly and comprehensively. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed the belief that the traditional friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to grow stronger and sincerely wished the friendly Syrian people greater progress and prosperity.
